Thank you very much for the review of the manuscript \textbf{Periodic Timers Revisited: the Real-time Embedded System Perspective}. We are glad that both reviewers have agreed that our paper has addressed all the comments from the first review. We have prepared a final version containing:

\begin{itemize}
	\item a list with 9 key words;
	\item an abstract with 145 words;
	\item a conclusion with 345 words that summarizes the paper and do not repeat the introduction;
	\item a short bio for each author that does not exceed 60 words;
\end{itemize}
	
In addition, we made a review to spell out each acronym in the first time it is used, to guarantee that all figures and tables are referred in the text, and to provide the complete information for all references. The final paper size was 18 pages using the double-spaced pages latex template (elsarticle, final, 3pd, times).

Looking forward to have the manuscript published,

